230
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:08,040
(The Phantom Knight
has had many story ideas.)

231
00:18:09,360 --> 00:18:12,080
(The most mature ones
were developed into novels,)

232
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:15,200
(but many more were
filed away for a long time.)

233
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:19,711
("My Life Envies No Immortal"
was the one we couldn't let go of.)

234
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:21,800
(It had a perfect start,)

235
00:18:22,088 --> 00:18:24,040
(but we couldn't find
an unconventional way)

236
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:25,644
(to complete the story's structure.)

237
00:18:27,066 --> 00:18:29,022
(It hasn't been
mentioned for so many years,)

238
00:18:29,488 --> 00:18:31,760
(but it turns out
we were both silently solving it.)

239
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:34,120
(Solving the story's problem,)

240
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:36,440
(and solving the one between us.)

241
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:49,840
When did you write this?

242
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:53,120
I thought you'd forgotten about it.

243
00:18:54,240 --> 00:18:55,600
When did you write it?

244
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:58,800
When Chenxing disbanded.

245
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,466
I wrote it a long time ago.

246
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:03,840
But to be fair,

247
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:06,311
it's actually written quite well.

248
00:19:09,066 --> 00:19:10,644
Your approach is a bit better.

249
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:12,880
Are you being serious?

250
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:14,960
You're suddenly so humble.

251
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,640
It feels a bit strange.

252
00:19:18,866 --> 00:19:20,488
The first half of yours is good,

253
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:22,200
but my ending is still a bit better.

254
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:28,120
Tell me,

255
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:32,120
why did we

256
00:19:33,320 --> 00:19:35,480
spend two months back then feeling like

257
00:19:35,666 --> 00:19:37,120
we couldn't keep the story going?

258
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:39,760
We were young.

259
00:19:40,511 --> 00:19:42,955
Back then, everything we wrote
was about never looking back,

260
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:44,320
being cold and heartless.

261
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:46,560
Now that we're older,

262
00:19:46,760 --> 00:19:47,440
we know.

263
00:19:48,866 --> 00:19:50,155
When it's time to turn back,

264
00:19:51,240 --> 00:19:52,200
you can still turn back.

265
00:20:12,040 --> 00:20:13,400
Is this realization a bit too late?

266
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:14,520
It's not.

267
00:20:14,844 --> 00:20:16,400
Your plane hasn't even taken off.

268
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:19,360
What?

269
00:20:19,360 --> 00:20:21,720
I mean, in this era
of rapid AI creation,

270
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:24,440
is the Phantom Knight's
realization too late?

271
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:28,280
Actually, I'm not interested
in competing with robots.

272
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:31,240
I just feel that,

273
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:33,880
in the face of massive AI creation,

274
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:35,920
the Phantom Knight

275
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:38,160
should have his own stance.

276
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:40,360
The Phantom Knight's standard

277
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:41,720
is to create good stories,

278
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:42,840
original stories.

279
00:20:43,822 --> 00:20:45,977
These aren't stories
that can be pieced together

280
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:47,400
by those familiar-looking

281
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:48,680
big data algorithms.

282
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:52,040
AI co-writing

283
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,200
will be the absolute trend
of the future.

284
00:20:57,711 --> 00:20:59,000
But He Han refuses to accept it.

285
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:01,920
Anyway, I'll just stop writing by then.

286
00:21:02,280 --> 00:21:03,600
If it's just to make a living,

287
00:21:03,680 --> 00:21:05,040
I can do anything.

288
00:21:06,360 --> 00:21:07,880
I choose to stay in the past.

289
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:10,040
Because humans make mistakes

290
00:21:10,520 --> 00:21:11,240
and get lazy.

291
00:21:11,666 --> 00:21:14,000
Even the Phantom Knight
has times when they can't go on,

292
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:14,600
right?

293
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:16,280
But AI won't.

294
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:18,240
That's so boring.

295
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:22,880
And you?

296
00:21:25,080 --> 00:21:26,080
I'll say it again.

297
00:21:26,977 --> 00:21:29,440
The Phantom Knight's
standard is to create good stories.

298
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:31,640
If AI can do that,

299
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:33,280
I won't reject it.

300
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:36,040
It's just that at that point,

301
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:38,080
it might be time for us,
the Phantom Knight,

302
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:40,000
to retire from the scene again.

303
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:46,280
Actually, besides Ma,

304
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:47,920
you're the only one who knew

305
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:49,240
that we were Phantom Knight.

306
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:52,080
I never understood why

307
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:53,640
you just suddenly disbanded.

308
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:55,840
I thought it was because

309
00:21:55,840 --> 00:21:57,040
of that unfinished novel,

310
00:21:57,160 --> 00:21:58,422
that you had a disagreement.

311
00:22:00,520 --> 00:22:01,800
I just remember back then,

312
00:22:02,720 --> 00:22:04,320
you were always fighting and making up.

313
00:22:08,240 --> 00:22:09,800
Actually, Phantom Knight didn't disband

314
00:22:10,840 --> 00:22:11,880
because of our arguments,

315
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:13,360
disagreements, or a breakup.

316
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:16,600
It was to stop
the fighting and disagreements,

317
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:18,440
so we could be together in peace.

318
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:25,200
Because one day, we suddenly realized

319
00:22:27,520 --> 00:22:29,400
that if we wrote a novel together,

320
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:31,880
things were great when they were good,

321
00:22:32,480 --> 00:22:34,040
but when they weren't, we'd fight.

322
00:22:34,822 --> 00:22:37,120
And when we were stuck,
we'd get anxious together.

323
00:22:39,040 --> 00:22:41,320
With a job that relies on inspiration,

324
00:22:43,040 --> 00:22:44,160
there was simply no way

325
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:46,088
for us to give each other
a stable future.

326
00:22:48,080 --> 00:22:49,600
(Year 2018)
What's with the silence?

327
00:22:49,680 --> 00:22:50,920
Can you just let me think?

328
00:22:52,480 --> 00:22:53,720
If you feel something is wrong,

329
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:54,400
you can say it.

330
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:56,040
We can discuss and talk about it.

331
00:22:56,755 --> 00:22:57,840
Yes, I think it's wrong.

332
00:22:57,960 --> 00:22:58,600
What's wrong?

333
00:22:58,920 --> 00:22:59,520
Tell me.

334
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:01,760
I think it's rigid,
predictable, and boring.

335
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:03,720
Well, give me something lively.

336
00:23:03,720 --> 00:23:04,880
Give me something interesting.

337
00:23:04,880 --> 00:23:06,240
Isn't that what I'm thinking about?

338
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:07,560
Anyway, yours won't work.

339
00:23:07,560 --> 00:23:08,000
Too conservative.

340
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:08,880
What conservative?

341
00:23:08,880 --> 00:23:11,280
If I weren't being conservative
and backing you up every time,

342
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:13,640
this would never
have made it this far, okay?

343
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:14,680
- How is that possible?
- Also,

344
00:23:14,680 --> 00:23:16,520
all creation needs
to follow its own rules,

345
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:17,000
doesn't it?

346
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:18,360
Rules? What the heck
is the point of rules?

347
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:19,760
Rules are meant to be broken.

348
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:21,560
Unless you want to be
a second-rate writer forever.

349
00:23:21,560 --> 00:23:24,200
And then what? After they're broken,
I have to clean up the mess?

350
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:25,040
No problem.

351
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:26,600
So what if you have to clean up a mess?

352
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:28,133
At least we would have taken that step.

353
00:23:28,140 --> 00:23:29,720
If you write a novel
by the book like this,

354
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:30,590
nobody's going to read it.

355
00:23:30,590 --> 00:23:32,520
- Don't you understand it yet?
- You're just being cryptic, you know?

356
00:23:32,520 --> 00:23:33,680
What's wrong with being cryptic?

357
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:36,400
People read Phantom Knight
exactly because our novel is different.

358
00:23:36,880 --> 00:23:37,480
Let me do it.

359
00:23:37,840 --> 00:23:39,080
I'll show you how to be cryptic.

360
00:23:40,520 --> 00:23:43,000
If I do it well, I'll write
this chapter. Just stay out of it.

361
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:44,320
What do you mean?

362
00:23:44,320 --> 00:23:46,040
Don't you dare post it on your own!

363
00:23:46,240 --> 00:23:48,800
- We must reach a consensus!
- We can't reach a consensus!

364
00:23:48,840 --> 00:23:50,880
Why can't we?
You're just giving me a flat "no."

365
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:51,880
You didn't even ask me.

366
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:52,880
This is creation.

367
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:54,000
Creation is a chaotic mess.

368
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:56,080
Nobody cares about being
polite and courteous, okay?

369
00:23:56,080 --> 00:23:57,280
Who's being polite and courteous?

370
00:23:57,280 --> 00:23:58,560
This is called mutual respect.

371
00:23:58,560 --> 00:24:00,920
Do I not respect you?
If anyone else said that to me today,

372
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:01,760
I would have walked out long ago.

373
00:24:01,760 --> 00:24:03,088
Then, go ahead and walk!

374
00:24:12,280 --> 00:24:14,120
And back then, we were considering

375
00:24:15,111 --> 00:24:16,911
whether or not we should get married.

376
00:24:26,644 --> 00:24:28,355
So I was the one who proposed it.

377
00:24:29,266 --> 00:24:30,400
Either we don't get married

378
00:24:31,360 --> 00:24:33,000
and keep being Phantom Knight together,

379
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:36,080
fighting until things
become irreconcilable

380
00:24:36,360 --> 00:24:37,120
and unbearable,

381
00:24:37,711 --> 00:24:39,844
and then we just disband
right then and there.

382
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:41,880
Or we get married,

383
00:24:42,280 --> 00:24:43,280
but one of us

384
00:24:43,280 --> 00:24:44,640
must step back to be an editor

385
00:24:45,080 --> 00:24:46,960
to provide support for the other.

386
00:24:48,111 --> 00:24:49,422
As for the creative side,

387
00:24:49,977 --> 00:24:51,555
it would center on one person.

388
00:24:56,240 --> 00:24:57,880
Between two people who were equals,

389
00:24:59,040 --> 00:25:00,120
how did you decide

390
00:25:00,880 --> 00:25:02,040
who would give up writing?

391
00:25:06,740 --> 00:25:10,660
(Year 2018)

392
00:25:10,660 --> 00:25:13,180
(Phantom Knight)

393
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:41,880
You first.

394
00:25:43,177 --> 00:25:44,333
Go ahead and draw.

395
00:25:44,680 --> 00:25:45,400
You do it.

396
00:25:59,700 --> 00:26:01,580
(Phantom Knight)

397
00:26:07,560 --> 00:26:08,120
You got it.

398
00:26:10,560 --> 00:26:11,000
No.

399
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:13,920
(Actually, I knew)

400
00:26:15,355 --> 00:26:17,177
(she had drawn Phantom Knight that day.)

401
00:26:32,980 --> 00:26:39,820
(Phantom Knight Design Studio)

402
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:41,360
So you drew Phantom Knight.

403
00:26:44,280 --> 00:26:45,200
Of course I knew

404
00:26:45,511 --> 00:26:47,360
that He Han wanted
to write novels forever.

405
00:26:51,040 --> 00:26:52,440
That's what I thought at the time.

406
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:54,320
Maybe that's what love is,

407
00:26:56,920 --> 00:26:57,840
being able to

408
00:26:58,440 --> 00:27:00,600
give up part of your dreams
for the other person.

409
00:27:04,880 --> 00:27:06,440
So later, I started Chenxing

410
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:08,760
with Zhao Lanxin and Ling Yikai.

411
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:12,760
We thought

412
00:27:13,360 --> 00:27:15,280
that we had found the right solution,

413
00:27:16,222 --> 00:27:18,000
that we could be like everyone else,

414
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:20,000
dating steadily,

415
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:22,760
and then moving into married life.

416
00:27:25,520 --> 00:27:26,760
But who could have guessed?

417
00:27:26,760 --> 00:27:28,480
We became editor and author,

418
00:27:29,280 --> 00:27:31,200
but we didn't fight
any less than before.

419
00:27:32,040 --> 00:27:33,240
The marriage never happened,

420
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:34,577
and the romance...

421
00:27:36,120 --> 00:27:36,880
Well, we broke up.

422
00:27:42,444 --> 00:27:44,377
The thing that stopped
you from being together

423
00:27:44,720 --> 00:27:45,840
wasn't Phantom Knight.

424
00:27:47,520 --> 00:27:49,440
Phantom Knight just
took the blame for you.

425
00:27:52,120 --> 00:27:53,040
It was ourselves.

426
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:54,960
He Han.

427
00:27:55,680 --> 00:27:56,320
Lin Zhanqiao.

428
00:27:59,000 --> 00:27:59,880
Two beautiful ladies,

429
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:03,000
stay a while longer.

430
00:28:03,960 --> 00:28:05,480
My shop is about to close.

431
00:28:05,800 --> 00:28:07,955
Closing again?
I thought you weren't going to.

432
00:28:08,600 --> 00:28:09,680
Just for a while.

433
00:28:10,440 --> 00:28:11,000
My son

434
00:28:11,600 --> 00:28:12,960
is taking me on a trip abroad.

435
00:28:14,120 --> 00:28:15,080
That's wonderful.

436
00:28:15,640 --> 00:28:16,800
You're really enjoying life.

437
00:28:17,440 --> 00:28:19,040
Let He Han know.

438
00:28:19,680 --> 00:28:20,160
I will.

439
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:22,400
I'll miss you guys.

440
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:23,600
Remember to

441
00:28:23,600 --> 00:28:25,200
take lots of photos for us to see.

442
00:28:26,480 --> 00:28:28,320
That's really kind of funny.

443
00:28:32,120 --> 00:28:32,560
Cheers.

444
00:28:32,733 --> 00:28:33,377
Come on.

445
00:28:36,800 --> 00:28:37,160
Cheers.

446
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:46,120
How do you think

447
00:28:46,244 --> 00:28:48,311
a villain should be
written to be convincing?

448
00:28:49,022 --> 00:28:50,311
You have to make him believe

449
00:28:50,440 --> 00:28:51,800
that he's the protagonist.

450
00:28:52,688 --> 00:28:53,960
You have to make him believe

451
00:28:54,177 --> 00:28:55,711
that he's the one in the right?

452
00:28:56,160 --> 00:28:56,640
Of course,

453
00:28:57,080 --> 00:28:58,400
a truly great villain

454
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:00,640
is never evil just for the sake of it.

455
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:02,480
He has his own worldview.

456
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:04,480
He feels the world owes him,

457
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:07,320
or he's more awake than everyone else,

458
00:29:07,680 --> 00:29:08,880
but nobody understands him.

459
00:29:10,600 --> 00:29:12,280
What if he wasn't
a villain to begin with?

460
00:29:12,777 --> 00:29:14,400
Then, it's even more interesting.

461
00:29:14,640 --> 00:29:17,200
Maybe he just wants to
prove his worth too much.

462
00:29:17,680 --> 00:29:18,840
He's afraid of being replaced.

463
00:29:19,088 --> 00:29:20,400
He's afraid of not being loved.

464
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:24,760
Then, how can

465
00:29:26,240 --> 00:29:27,960
a villain get the love he wants?

466
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:30,280
Is love really what he wants?

467
00:29:31,280 --> 00:29:31,840
What else?

468
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:34,040
Maybe it's recognition.

469
00:29:34,360 --> 00:29:35,320
Maybe it's control.

470
00:29:35,760 --> 00:29:38,200
Maybe he just wants to prove
he's worthy of love.

471
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:42,400
And if he never gets it?

472
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:44,200
He won't give up

473
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:46,560
until he's trapped himself in this game.

474
00:29:48,640 --> 00:29:49,640
That doesn't sound

475
00:29:50,160 --> 00:29:51,560
like a good ending.

476
00:29:52,280 --> 00:29:53,240
But he himself

477
00:29:53,320 --> 00:29:55,000
might not accept that ending.

478
00:29:57,580 --> 00:29:58,220
(AI Co-Writing)

479
00:31:02,040 --> 00:31:02,760
Hello, Ms. Zhao.

480
00:31:02,780 --> 00:31:04,380
(Chenxing Culture)

481
00:31:04,400 --> 00:31:05,520
Mr. Fan sent me here

482
00:31:05,520 --> 00:31:07,511
(Copyright Agreement)
to sign the agreements with you.

483
00:31:07,560 --> 00:31:09,000
Once you have finished signing,

484
00:31:09,040 --> 00:31:10,511
the work will be handed over to me.

485
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:12,960
Thank you, Ms. Zhao!

486
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:14,480
Thank you.

487
00:31:14,511 --> 00:31:15,080
It's nothing.

488
00:31:15,080 --> 00:31:15,880
Thank you so much.

489
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:17,800
Colleagues of the Brain-on-Paper Team,
are you happy?

490
00:31:17,920 --> 00:31:18,760
Yes!

491
00:31:18,760 --> 00:31:21,000
From now on, we have our lucky star.

492
00:31:21,120 --> 00:31:22,240
- I can make a living writing novels.
- Everyone says it's great!

493
00:31:22,240 --> 00:31:23,040
The first one who sells their copyrights

494
00:31:23,040 --> 00:31:24,640
- must treat the whole team!
- I'll give you the contract today.

495
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:25,880
- Let's eat lobster!
- Ms. Zhao?

496
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:26,600
Ms. Zhao.

497
00:31:27,711 --> 00:31:28,320
What's wrong?

498
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:28,760
Ms. Zhao!

499
00:31:28,880 --> 00:31:30,160
- Are you okay?
- What's happening?

500
00:31:30,160 --> 00:31:30,720
Call 120.

501
00:31:48,100 --> 00:31:49,180
(So what do we do next?)

502
00:31:49,180 --> 00:31:49,920
(First,)

503
00:31:51,110 --> 00:31:52,700
(when chasing Fan Sizhe...)

504
00:31:52,950 --> 00:31:53,470
(Second...)

505
00:31:55,530 --> 00:31:57,066
Why aren't you answering your phone?

506
00:31:57,070 --> 00:31:57,990
What are you doing here?

507
00:31:58,000 --> 00:31:58,740
I didn't hear it.

508
00:31:58,760 --> 00:31:59,640
Zhao Lanxin is in premature labor.

509
00:31:59,640 --> 00:32:00,844
Come with me to the hospital.

510
00:32:03,822 --> 00:32:05,488
Your children are about to be born.

511
00:32:19,866 --> 00:32:20,844
I'm not going.

512
00:32:22,622 --> 00:32:24,222
I had an agreement with Zhao Lanxin.

513
00:32:24,488 --> 00:32:26,600
We'll get a divorce
once the children are born.

514
00:32:27,866 --> 00:32:29,444
She will take the children away.

515
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:31,880
So when I see them,

516
00:32:32,422 --> 00:32:33,880
it also means I'm about to lose them.

517
00:32:35,888 --> 00:32:36,844
What's the point?

518
00:32:38,320 --> 00:32:38,720
Just go.

519
00:32:39,911 --> 00:32:42,355
Let me know
when the children are born. Thanks.

520
00:35:36,280 --> 00:35:37,800
I've revised it exactly as you said.

521
00:35:38,280 --> 00:35:40,200
Let me pass this time, Ms. Lin.

522
00:35:40,200 --> 00:35:41,644
I still have to go drive later.

523
00:35:45,040 --> 00:35:45,680
Not bad.

524
00:35:50,040 --> 00:35:51,160
Our current progress

525
00:35:51,400 --> 00:35:52,840
is significantly ahead of schedule.

526
00:35:53,088 --> 00:35:54,280
In another two or three months,

527
00:35:54,280 --> 00:35:55,440
the novel will be finished.

528
00:35:55,800 --> 00:35:56,640
Isn't that great?

529
00:35:57,240 --> 00:35:57,680
Yeah.

530
00:35:58,240 --> 00:36:00,120
But what do we do when it's finished?

531
00:36:00,533 --> 00:36:01,666
Start another one?

532
00:36:01,920 --> 00:36:03,000
We'll see then.

533
00:36:03,920 --> 00:36:05,760
This doesn't sound like you,
Lin Zhanqiao.

534
00:36:08,822 --> 00:36:09,888
How about this?

535
00:36:10,600 --> 00:36:11,720
After the novel is finished,

536
00:36:12,920 --> 00:36:14,240
let's go get married.

537
00:36:21,440 --> 00:36:22,480
Are you serious?

538
00:36:23,040 --> 00:36:23,480
Of course.

539
00:36:42,520 --> 00:36:43,200
Look,

540
00:36:45,120 --> 00:36:46,040
we have been

541
00:36:47,880 --> 00:36:49,280
bickering like this,

542
00:36:49,711 --> 00:36:51,333
breaking up and making up.

543
00:36:54,120 --> 00:36:55,720
We disbanded Phantom Knight back then

544
00:36:56,800 --> 00:36:57,520
because we

545
00:36:58,240 --> 00:37:00,000
wanted to get closer to each other.

546
00:37:02,800 --> 00:37:04,760
Now, we've reformed Phantom Knight

547
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:06,480
also because

548
00:37:07,200 --> 00:37:08,920
we want to get closer to each other.

549
00:37:18,560 --> 00:37:19,720
But is it possible

550
00:37:23,680 --> 00:37:25,400
that the distance of this collaboration

551
00:37:27,520 --> 00:37:28,320
is actually

552
00:37:29,520 --> 00:37:30,920
the most suitable distance

553
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:33,000
between us?

554
00:37:42,155 --> 00:37:43,511
One step further and it's too far,

555
00:37:45,533 --> 00:37:46,840
then we'll miss each other.

556
00:37:48,977 --> 00:37:50,622
One step closer and it's too near,

557
00:37:56,022 --> 00:37:57,511
then we'll hurt each other.

558
00:38:22,080 --> 00:38:23,040
It's my fault.

559
00:38:26,600 --> 00:38:27,920
It's our fault.

560
00:38:37,840 --> 00:38:38,440
Lin Zhanqiao,

561
00:38:40,355 --> 00:38:41,444
I love you very much.

562
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:46,560
Me too.

563
00:38:50,080 --> 00:38:51,440
Even more than very much.

564
00:39:03,933 --> 00:39:05,560
(He Han and I have come full circle.)

565
00:39:06,511 --> 00:39:09,111
(We seem to have returned to
how we first loved each other.)

566
00:39:10,560 --> 00:39:11,360
(But I know,)

567
00:39:12,520 --> 00:39:13,160
(this time)

568
00:39:14,440 --> 00:39:15,640
(is different from the past.)

569
00:39:19,980 --> 00:39:24,820
(Phantom Knight Design Studio)

570
00:39:37,680 --> 00:39:38,560
Lin Zhanqiao!

571
00:39:40,440 --> 00:39:42,160
Is Phantom Knight still continuing?

572
00:39:44,080 --> 00:39:44,680
Of course.

573
00:39:50,680 --> 00:39:53,680
(I'm more certain about
my choices and my stance.)

574
00:39:54,600 --> 00:39:57,080
(I see my future self more clearly.)

575
00:39:58,840 --> 00:40:00,040
(We love each other deeply,)

576
00:40:00,644 --> 00:40:02,760
(but we're willing to
give each other freedom)

577
00:40:03,640 --> 00:40:05,120
(and give ourselves space.)

578
00:40:06,960 --> 00:40:07,840
(We dare to promise)

579
00:40:07,840 --> 00:40:10,288
(to be each other's
first responder in times of need,)

580
00:40:11,111 --> 00:40:12,240
(no matter the distance)

581
00:40:13,480 --> 00:40:14,320
(and at any cost.)

582
00:40:18,760 --> 00:40:19,560
(I didn't leave.)

583
00:40:20,640 --> 00:40:21,680
(Zhou Mei, however, did.)

584
00:40:22,577 --> 00:40:24,520
(She only told me
she was gone afterward.)

585
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:28,480
(She said it was revenge
for me not telling her I stayed.)

586
00:40:29,680 --> 00:40:30,560
(Actually, I think)

587
00:40:31,088 --> 00:40:34,133
(it's because she didn't want to
face the sorrow of parting so often.)

588
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:37,520
(She finally let go of the past)

589
00:40:38,480 --> 00:40:40,080
(and cleared the thorns from her life.)

590
00:40:41,440 --> 00:40:42,400
(A brand-new Zhou Mei)

591
00:40:42,711 --> 00:40:43,960
(will go and bravely embrace)

592
00:40:44,133 --> 00:40:45,680
(the person truly worthy of her love.)

593
00:40:46,320 --> 00:40:47,120
Thank you, everyone.

594
00:40:47,320 --> 00:40:48,240
I'll keep working hard.

595
00:40:49,066 --> 00:40:51,488
(Zhangzhu terminated
her contract with Lingqi Platform)

596
00:40:51,755 --> 00:40:53,120
(and signed with Dingqi Platform.)

597
00:40:54,240 --> 00:40:55,160
(And she won)

598
00:40:55,600 --> 00:40:57,200
(the New Creator Award.)

599
00:40:57,940 --> 00:40:59,740
("Han" Overdose)

600
00:41:05,222 --> 00:41:06,520
(After the babies were born,)

601
00:41:07,133 --> 00:41:09,440
(Zhao Lanxin and Ling Yikai's
relationship softened.)

602
00:41:10,680 --> 00:41:11,880
(They moved their battleground)

603
00:41:11,933 --> 00:41:13,990
(to the trivialities of
domestic life and parenting.)

604
00:41:15,400 --> 00:41:16,040
(Zhao Lanxin)

605
00:41:16,520 --> 00:41:19,000
(still holds high the banner
with her own name on it.)

606
00:41:20,222 --> 00:41:21,488
(She doesn't complain,)

607
00:41:21,844 --> 00:41:23,244
(and she doesn't give up.)

608
00:41:33,488 --> 00:41:34,560
(Then, there's San Mei.)

609
00:41:35,533 --> 00:41:36,680
(Of the original trio,)

610
00:41:37,320 --> 00:41:38,560
(the other two drifted away.)

611
00:41:40,080 --> 00:41:41,600
(Even without any other advantages,)

612
00:41:42,977 --> 00:41:43,920
(as long as a woman)

613
00:41:44,560 --> 00:41:45,720
(is diligent and brave,)

614
00:41:46,720 --> 00:41:48,240
(she can always find a way)

615
00:41:48,666 --> 00:41:50,600
(to make a living and find her place.)

616
00:41:58,444 --> 00:42:00,800
(Minors Not Allowed)
(We've each found our own path.)

617
00:42:02,200 --> 00:42:02,960
(In family,)

618
00:42:03,400 --> 00:42:04,000
(friendship,)

619
00:42:04,600 --> 00:42:05,080
(romance,)

620
00:42:05,760 --> 00:42:06,480
(and marriage,)

621
00:42:06,960 --> 00:42:08,960
(we've each found our rightful place.)

622
00:42:10,560 --> 00:42:11,720
(There are no myths in love.)

623
00:42:12,680 --> 00:42:14,960
(The prince-and-princess script
isn't in our hands.)

624
00:42:15,880 --> 00:42:19,120
(And we certainly can't
write a happily ever after ending.)

625
00:42:21,080 --> 00:42:22,120
(In an ordinary life,)

626
00:42:22,555 --> 00:42:24,511
(if it's destined to be
a mix of joy and sorrow,)

627
00:42:25,480 --> 00:42:26,520
(then in moments of joy,)

628
00:42:26,733 --> 00:42:29,444
(I hope there's someone to
share a glass of sweet wine with.)

629
00:42:29,911 --> 00:42:31,200
(And in times of distress,)

630
00:42:32,040 --> 00:42:32,960
(we shall surely)

631
00:42:33,888 --> 00:42:35,644
(stand together, side by side.)

632
00:43:05,921 --> 00:43:07,041
(I've been thinking.)

633
00:43:08,321 --> 00:43:11,601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

634
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:19,691
(is probably different.)

635
00:43:20,691 --> 00:43:22,441
♪If the sky♪

636
00:43:22,951 --> 00:43:24,351
♪And the sea♪

637
00:43:24,891 --> 00:43:26,601
♪Turned upside down♪

638
00:43:28,161 --> 00:43:30,091
♪If a swimming fish♪

639
00:43:30,491 --> 00:43:33,881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

640
00:43:35,651 --> 00:43:37,621
♪If back then♪

641
00:43:37,981 --> 00:43:42,391
♪We had never let go♪

642
00:43:42,991 --> 00:43:49,271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

643
00:43:50,391 --> 00:43:52,541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

644
00:43:52,541 --> 00:43:54,411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

645
00:43:54,591 --> 00:43:57,031
♪And found our way back whole♪

646
00:43:57,871 --> 00:44:00,041
♪So let this surging love♪

647
00:44:00,041 --> 00:44:04,471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

648
00:44:05,371 --> 00:44:07,551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

649
00:44:07,551 --> 00:44:08,641
♪That's alright♪

650
00:44:09,181 --> 00:44:09,931
♪If we're buried♪

651
00:44:09,931 --> 00:44:12,631
♪By passing years all the better♪

652
00:44:12,891 --> 00:44:15,071
♪At least we still can keep♪

653
00:44:15,251 --> 00:44:19,671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

654
00:44:35,431 --> 00:44:37,721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

655
00:44:37,721 --> 00:44:39,481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

656
00:44:39,601 --> 00:44:42,071
♪Searching all along the way♪

657
00:44:42,871 --> 00:44:45,031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

658
00:44:45,221 --> 00:44:50,131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

659
00:44:50,131 --> 00:44:53,651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

660
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:54,861
♪Only after loss♪

661
00:44:54,861 --> 00:44:57,491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

662
00:44:57,901 --> 00:45:00,261
♪In another time and space♪

663
00:45:00,261 --> 00:45:01,821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

664
00:45:01,821 --> 00:45:04,651
♪Till we grow old♪

665
00:45:05,611 --> 00:45:07,901
♪But still the sky will never♪

666
00:45:07,901 --> 00:45:10,571
♪Turn with the sea♪

667
00:45:13,091 --> 00:45:15,501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

668
00:45:15,501 --> 00:45:20,711
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪

